node.text: I've been in so many videos about wildfire prevention over the lasty 74 years. Who remembers this cartoon from the1960s? #OnlyYou #SmokeyBear75

node.title: Smokey Bear and the Little Boy

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Smokey Bear on August 02, 2021. May be a cartoon of standing and tree.

node.text: Did you know that you can design and download your own free Smokey Bear coloring book? Celebrate #NationalColoringBookDay by creating your own by visiting Smokey for Kids at SmokeyBear.com

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Smokey Bear on July 30, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing, tree and outdoors.

node.text: Anybody who helps prevent wildfires is a friend of mine. Happy #DayofFriendship, tag a friend who loves the environment as much as you do! (📷: @aubreyhays)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Smokey Bear on July 28, 2021. May be an image of deer, outdoors and text that says 'GRIZZLY PEAK Please. Please,Mister, Mister, DON'T BE CARELESS PREVENT FOREST FIRES Greater danger than ever!'.

node.text: A little wildfire prevention trivia for ya - who knows where to spot this sign? Hint: it's the happiest place on earth 💫

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Smokey Bear on July 26, 2021. May be a cartoon of tree and text that says 'PROTECT WHAT YOU LOVE PREVENT WIL WILDFIRES COUNCIL TA BeOutdoorSafe.org'.

node.text: Summer nights around a campfire are the best, but let's enjoy them safely! Aways check for local burn bans and make sure the fire is out. Drown, stir, down, feel - if it's too hot to touch, it's too hot to leave! For more tips to #BeOutdoorSafe, visit BeOutdoorsafe.org

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Smokey Bear on July 24, 2021. May be a cartoon of 1 person and text that says 'Smokey Says: CRUSH IT! BREAK IT! SMOKEY DROWN IT! USE IT! Remember- Only you can PREVENT FOREST FIRES!'.

node.text: A single match or cigarette can cause a wildfire. Dispose of them carefully every time.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Smokey Bear on July 22, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and standing.

node.text: Thinking of my pal, the late Alex Trebek. Happy Birthday to the legend, we all miss you.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Smokey Bear on July 21, 2021. May be an image of nature.

node.text:
Please be vigilant and careful when outdoors this wildfire season. Nearly nine out of ten wildfires are started by humans. Conditions are very dry and the risk of starting a wildfire is high this year. Visit SmokeyBear.com for helpful wildfire prevention tips. 

With warmer, dryer conditions, wildfires are getting tougher to put out. If you live in or are visiting an area with active wildfires, check the interactive wildfire maps on InciWeb (inciweb.nwcg.gov) and listen to local authorities for instructions to stay safe. (📷: @LATimes)

node.text: When chains drag on the road, they leave sparks. And sparks can cause a wildfire - especially if you're in a drought like the West. Please be careful, cross those chains!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Smokey Bear on July 17, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and standing.

node.text: 🐻👉🚫🔥🌲 It's #WorldEmojiDay, how's your emoji game? Tell me how #OnlyYou will prevent wildfires, emojis only! 👇

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Smokey Bear on July 16, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'ONLY 75t SMOKEY YOU! EST. 1944'.

node.text: I love when artists imagine me in their style! Thank you @gabo.ghoul for this retro rendition! Have you made any Smokey Bear art? Tag me, I'd love to see!

node.text: As my pal alroker says, wildfires can happen anywhere - even in your neck of the woods! When there are parched and windy conditions, you've got to be extra careful with fire. #OnlyYou can prevent unwanted, human-caused wildfires
